description: Numerators of coefficients in function a(x) such that a(a(a(x))) = sinh x.
references: W. C. Yang, Composition equations, preprint, 1999.
mathematica: n = 15; m (* = maximal degree *)= 2n - 1; a[x_] = Sum[c[k]*x^k, {k, 1, m, 2}]; coes = DeleteCases[ CoefficientList[ Series[ a@a@a@x - Sinh[x], {x, 0, m}], x] // Rest, 0]; Do[s[k] = Solve[coes[[1]] == 0] // First; coes = coes /. s[k] // Rest, {k, 1, n}]; (CoefficientList[a[x] /. Flatten@Array[s, n], x] // Numerator // Partition[#, 2] &)[[All, 2]] (* _Jean-Fran√ßois Alcover_, Jan 04 2013 *)
